.DT
set_salinity
Disk World creator help
set_salinity

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
set_salinity -  This function sets the salinity of the water as an integer variable between 0 and 100.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void set_salinity(int how_salty)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^how_salty%^RESET%^ - the new salinity of the water
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/room/basic/water.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This function sets the salinity of the water as an integer variable between
0 and 100.  Higher salinity will have a small positive effect on the
buoyancy of objects in the room.  The default salinity is 0.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
query_salinity, calc_buoyancy

.EP

